
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ANALYSIS PHASE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From the directory containing this INSTALL file:

    $ perl configure.pl

    configuring svtools, version 0.0.1
    checking prerequisites ......
    generating svtools program target
    done
    created svtools program target:
      /path/to/svtools-0.0.1/svtools

Perform a quick check for appropriate installation by calling svtools with
no commands or options:
 
    $ ./svtools

    svtools version 0.0.1
    applications for exploring paired-end sequencing data for structural variants
    usage:	svtools <command> [options ...]
    use 'svtools --help' or 'svtools <command> --help' for extended help

In most cases you will want to add ‘/path/to/svtools-<#.#.#>’ to  
your system PATH variable so that it is available to you from any directory 
by simply typing svtools.  

Familiarize yourself with svtools as follows:

    $ svtools --help
    $ cat README
    

